$ PowerShell cmdLet New-ScheduledTaskAction
@ new-scheduledTaskAction

`new-scheduledTaskAction` returns a `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/Microsoft/Management/Infrastructure/CimInstance` object which represents a command that a task executes when the → Windows/services/installed/Schedule[Task Scheduler] runs the task.

sa:

 `→ Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/scheduledTask/register`

  → Windows/services/installed/Schedule#task-scheduler-ps-at-startup

